# MCP Client Wiring ā€” hal0

Connect external tools (Claude Code, OpenWebUI, etc.) to hal0's MCP servers.

## Available MCP Servers

| Server | URL | Transport | Description |
|--------|-----|-----------|-------------|
| hal0-admin | `http://127.0.0.1:8080/mcp/admin/mcp` | `http` (POST-only) | Slot/model management, system admin, hardware probes |
| hal0-memory | `http://127.0.0.1:8080/mcp/memory/mcp` | `http` (POST-only) | Cognee vector/graph memory, agent identity cards |

**Important:** hal0 MCP servers only support plain HTTP POST transport. Do NOT use `streamable-http` or SSE ā€” these will fail with HTTP 406 or 405.

## Quick Start

```bash
hal0 connect claude-code
```

This auto-discovers MCP servers and wires them into your client. Supports `--dry-run` to preview, `--repair` to fix misconfigurations.

## Manual Configuration

### Claude Code (`~/.claude/settings.json`)

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "hal0-admin": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "http://127.0.0.1:8080/mcp/admin/mcp"
    },
    "hal0-memory": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "http://127.0.0.1:8080/mcp/memory/mcp"
    }
  }
}
```

Add permissions in the same file:

```json
{
  "permissions": {
    "allow": [
      "mcp__hal0-admin__*",
      "mcp__hal0-memory__*"
    ]
  }
}
```

### Other MCP Clients

Any MCP-compatible client with HTTP transport support. Key requirements:

- **Transport:** `http` (plain POST, NOT streamable-http or SSE)
- **URL suffix:** Always ends with `/mcp` (e.g. `/mcp/admin/mcp`, not `/mcp/admin`)
- **Headers:** Set `X-hal0-Agent: <your-agent-id>` for identity routing
- **Memory namespace:** Set `X-hal0-Private: 1` to access private memory namespaces

## Verification

Test a connection manually:

```bash
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/mcp/admin/mcp \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"tools/list","id":1}' | jq '.result.tools | length'
```

Should return the tool count (typically 25+ for admin, 4 for memory).

## Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Likely Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------------|-----|
| HTTP 405 Method Not Allowed | URL missing `/mcp` suffix (e.g. `/mcp/admin`) | Use full path: `/mcp/admin/mcp` |
| HTTP 406 Not Acceptable | Using `streamable-http` transport (sends GET + POST) | Use `http` transport (POST-only) |
| Connection refused | hal0 API not running | `systemctl status hal0-api` |
| Unknown tool | MCP server not connected | Run `hal0 connect <client>` |

